I had created some stashes in the previous version of Sourcetree(version 2.6 probably). I got a notice for the update to 2.7. I installed the updated. After the update, I can no longer diff individual stashes. They all show up in the list of stashes but if I click on a stash in the list, the right pane will just show the loading icon. If I try to apply the stash by right clicking on it, I get the following error:
{quote}git -c diff.mnemonicprefix=false -c core.quotepath=false -c credential.helper=sourcetree stash pop stash@\{0}

One or more of this task's arguments is invalid. They cannot start with '-', and must follow git ref-format rules: https://www.kernel.org/pub/software/scm/git/docs/git-check-ref-format.html

Completed with errors, see above
{quote}
I was able to view the and apply the stashes with the git cli.

Applying stashes has started consistently failing with an error (see below). Viewing stashes doesn't work either, probably for the same underlying reason; when I select a stash the main pane goes blank with a progress indicator that never goes away.

The error sheet reads:
{quote}git -c diff.mnemonicprefix=false -c core.quotepath=false -c credential.helper=sourcetree stash pop stash@\{0} 

One or more of this task's arguments is invalid. They cannot start with '-', and must follow git ref-format rules: https://www.kernel.org/pub/software/scm/git/docs/git-check-ref-format.html
{quote}

App is unusable, even after app restart and machine restart


